[DQR.IFRS.0008.6819] The calculation in the extension taxonomy rolling up from CashFlowsFromUsedInOperatingActivities to CashFlowsFromUsedInOperations in 05 - Rapport över kassaflöden is the opposite of a calculation defined in the base taxonomy. Check that the calculation is correct or that you have used the correct tag for the two elements identified in the calculation It is possible that the calculation is correct in the case of a reconciliation calculation. Check that the concept CashFlowsFromUsedInOperations is the correct calculation parent for this element.

[DQR.US.0101.9538] The concept ifrs-full:InterestPaidClassifiedAsOperatingActivities appears in the financing cashflows of the companies cash flow statement. ifrs-full:InterestPaidClassifiedAsOperatingActivities is an operating item and it is expected that this item would only appear in the cash flow from operating activities. Please review the calculations defined for the cash flow statement to determine that the correct element has been used for this item.
